Dear Hiring Team, 

It is with great pleasure that I submit my candidacy for the *Applications Engineer* position with *OSI Optoelectronics*. I bring over three years of professional experience in technical specification development, cross-functional collaboration, and customer-facing technical support, along with a strong academic foundation as a Master of Science in Computer Science graduate from Pace University, NY with a 4.0 GPA.

Through my experience across two engineering roles, I have built and delivered production-grade systems that directly reflect the technical depth and customer collaboration this position demands. As a Software Engineer at Sperse, I developed technical specifications and API documentation for 1,000+ platform endpoints, translating customer requirements into validated tool calls and enabling automated customer actions across complex workflows — requiring rigorous requirements gathering, proposal development, and clear communication with both internal stakeholders and end customers. I established test procedures, assembly procedures, and evaluation hooks using Langfuse and LangSmith for tracing, structured logs, and quality monitoring, enabling systematic troubleshooting and root cause analysis of system failures. I performed cost analysis and optimization of system architecture, reducing end-to-end latency by 60% and lowering API costs by 50% through routing improvements and concurrency tuning — demonstrating the cost-effective design thinking and continuous improvement mindset this role requires. Prior to Sperse, as a Software Engineer at Qualitest, I designed and developed a cloud-agnostic Storage Service using Python, PostgreSQL, and Redis handling file operations across Google Cloud Storage, S3, and MinIO, requiring cost-effective design and vendor qualification across multiple cloud providers. I also built an internal support chatbot using LangChain and RAG with PostgreSQL vector store, reducing average ticket resolution time by 20% through technical support automation — giving me direct experience providing technical customer support and troubleshooting complex issues. I contributed to an Identity & Access Management platform development using React, Spring Boot, and AWS, supporting thousands of users across 30+ applications with rigorous quality assurance and cross-functional collaboration with engineering and QA teams, and developed backend workflows using AWS Step Functions to handle long-running data import jobs, establishing test and assembly procedures for prototype builds and production transfer. Together, these roles have prepared me to generate cost sheets, communicate with customers for new OEM opportunities, propose feasible and cost-effective designs, establish test and assembly procedures, and provide technical customer support — the core responsibilities of this Applications Engineer position.

My academic research experience has given me a rigorous foundation in technical documentation, quality assurance protocols, and technical training — skills that translate directly into the engineering discipline and collaborative culture OSI Optoelectronics values. As an AI Researcher at the Pace Artificial Intelligence Lab, I conducted applied research on StyleGAN and Stable Diffusion for generating industry-standard designs, utilizing CUDA, PyTorch and LORA on Pace University's HPC cluster for model training. I developed test procedures and quality assurance protocols for model inference using vLLM with Hugging Face deployment, ensuring secure and efficient model serving. Beyond building the systems myself, I delivered technical training workshops on GPU programming with CUDA and Mojo, and on building AI Agents, for 50+ students, creating technical documentation and hands-on materials. Designing and delivering those sessions required me to break down complex technical concepts clearly and accessibly — directly mirroring the technical customer support and communication responsibilities central to this role. This experience has shaped me into an engineer who builds with rigor, documents with precision, and communicates with clarity, all of which I would bring to OSI Optoelectronics and its mission.

I have always been passionate about innovation and teamwork in developing breakthrough technology solutions, and I am deeply aligned with OSI Systems' mission to make the world a safer and healthier place. I envision myself contributing my technical expertise and customer-focused approach to furthering OSI Optoelectronics' leadership in optoelectronic devices for aerospace, defense, medical, and industrial applications. I would love to discuss my interest in this position with your team and can be reached at #ph or #eml. Thank you for your time and consideration, I look forward to connecting!

